<tr id="L326"><td><a href="#L326">326</a></td><td>GARAK:  She's been Tain's housekeeper and confidant for over thirty years.</td></tr>

<tr id="L327"><td><a href="#L327">327</a></td><td>ODO:  She seemed almost fond of you.</td></tr>

<tr id="L328"><td><a href="#L328">328</a></td><td>GARAK:  Is it so hard to believe that there's one person in this galaxy who could regard me with a certain affection?</td></tr>

<tr id="L329"><td><a href="#L329">329</a></td><td>ODO:  I could believe there's one but I wouldn't expect it to be someone who worked for Enabran Tain. As I understand it, the two of you didn't part on the best of terms.</td></tr>

<tr id="L330"><td><a href="#L330">330</a></td><td>GARAK:  You could say that. Tain was directly responsible for my exile from Cardassia.</td></tr>

<tr id="L331"><td><a href="#L331">331</a></td><td>ODO:  Then I don't understand</td></tr>

<tr id="L332"><td><a href="#L332">332</a></td><td>GARAK:  Why I would be risking my life to help him?</td></tr>

<tr id="L333"><td><a href="#L333">333</a></td><td>ODO:  Exactly.</td></tr>

<tr id="L334"><td><a href="#L334">334</a></td><td>GARAK:  Yes, I can see how that would be puzzling.</td></tr>

<tr id="L335"><td><a href="#L335">335</a></td><td>ODO:  All right. You owe him something.</td></tr>

<tr id="L336"><td><a href="#L336">336</a></td><td>GARAK:  A logical deduction. I see why you're the constable.</td></tr>

<tr id="L337"><td><a href="#L337">337</a></td><td>ODO:  But it's more than that. He means something to you. Something personal?</td></tr>

<tr id="L338"><td><a href="#L338">338</a></td><td>GARAK:  Ah, now you've just moved from deduction to supposition.</td></tr>

<tr id="L339"><td><a href="#L339">339</a></td><td>ODO:  You're not the kind of man who would go to such lengths simply to repay a debt.</td></tr>

<tr id="L340"><td><a href="#L340">340</a></td><td>GARAK:  Are you trying to say that I have no sense of honour?</td></tr>

<tr id="L341"><td><a href="#L341">341</a></td><td>ODO:  That remains to be seen.</td></tr>

<tr id="L342"><td><a href="#L342">342</a></td><td>GARAK:  Yes.</td></tr>

<tr id="L343"><td><a href="#L343">343</a></td><td>ODO:  You wouldn't risk going into Cardassian space for just anyone. It would have to be someone important to you, someone you cared about. I think you were more than Tain's advisor. I think you were his protg and he was your mentor. That is, until he sent you into exile. And yet, despite that, you care enough about him to risk your life for him. Or is all that just supposition?</td></tr>

<tr id="L344"><td><a href="#L344">344</a></td><td>GARAK:  A very interesting analysis. Very interesting. Particularly coming from you.</td></tr>

<tr id="L345"><td><a href="#L345">345</a></td><td>ODO:  Oh?</td></tr>

<tr id="L346"><td><a href="#L346">346</a></td><td>GARAK:  It's been my observation that you always act from a sense of justice, or at least what you consider justice. There's no feeling behind what you do, no emotion beyond a certain distaste for loose ends and disorder. You don't know what it means to care about someone, do you? People are just interesting creatures to be studied and analysed.</td></tr>

<tr id="L347"><td><a href="#L347">347</a></td><td>ODO:  Is there any point to this?</td></tr>

<tr id="L348"><td><a href="#L348">348</a></td><td>GARAK:  Only that I find it interesting that you ascribe feelings and motivations to me that you know nothing about. Or am I wrong? Tell me, is there one person in this universe you do care for? One person who's more than just an interesting puzzle to be solved. Is there, Odo? Anyone?</td></tr>

<tr id="L349"><td><a href="#L349">349</a></td><td>ODO:  If there were, I certainly wouldn't tell you.</td></tr>

<tr id="L350"><td><a href="#L350">350</a></td><td>GARAK:  And that would be a wise decision.</td></tr>

