<tr id="L397"><td><a href="#L397">397</a></td><td>TAIN:  True. They should never have hired the Flaxian to blow up your shop.</td></tr>

<tr id="L398"><td><a href="#L398">398</a></td><td>GARAK:  Actually, I blew up my shop. It was a way of piquing the interest of the good constable.</td></tr>

<tr id="L399"><td><a href="#L399">399</a></td><td>TAIN:  You blew up your own shop? You, my friend, are a true original. If you hadn't betrayed me, things would have been very different.</td></tr>

<tr id="L400"><td><a href="#L400">400</a></td><td>GARAK:  I never betrayed you! At least, not in my heart. Why do you think I'm here? I came because I thought the Romulans were trying to kill you. I came here to save you.</td></tr>

<tr id="L401"><td><a href="#L401">401</a></td><td>TAIN:  I never thought I'd hear myself say this, Garak, but I believe you. You can go.</td></tr>

