<tr id="L407"><td><a href="#L407">407</a></td><td>TAIN:  It's too late. Central Command will have a war on its hands, whether it wants one or not. And as for Starfleet, this isn't their fight. They won't interfere.</td></tr>

<tr id="L408"><td><a href="#L408">408</a></td><td>ODO:  It's a trick, Garak. After all this, he won't let you just walk away.</td></tr>

<tr id="L409"><td><a href="#L409">409</a></td><td>TAIN:  It's not a trick, it's a choice. You can walk out that door, or join me.</td></tr>

<tr id="L410"><td><a href="#L410">410</a></td><td>GARAK:  Join you?</td></tr>

<tr id="L411"><td><a href="#L411">411</a></td><td>TAIN:  That is what you've been waiting for, isn't it? To end your exile, to come back into the fold. I'm asking you to serve Cardassia again, by my side.</td></tr>

<tr id="L412"><td><a href="#L412">412</a></td><td>GARAK:  Well you'll pardon me if I appear a little startled, but are you saying that all is forgiven?</td></tr>

<tr id="L413"><td><a href="#L413">413</a></td><td>TAIN:  I can't forgive what you did but I can try to forget, to put it aside as if it never happened. So, do you want to go back to your shop and hem pants or shall we pick up where we left off?</td></tr>

<tr id="L414"><td><a href="#L414">414</a></td><td>ODO:  Garak, this is the man who put you into exile. This is the man who just two days ago tried to have you killed.</td></tr>

<tr id="L415"><td><a href="#L415">415</a></td><td>GARAK:  Yes, he is. But it doesn't matter. I'm back.</td></tr>

